.TH "funzy_enterkey" "1" "2026-06-09" "" "funzyto770 User Manuals"
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
funzy_enterkey - interactively define the keyboard layout for funzyto770
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]funzy_enterkey\f[R]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]funzy_enterkey\f[R] is an interactive X11 utility that creates the
keyboard layout file \f[B]keyto7\f[R] required by
\f[B]funzyto770\f[R](1).
It prompts the user to press each of the 68 keys one by one: 58 TO7
keyboard keys and 10 joystick directions and buttons (5 per joystick).
.PP
The program opens an empty X11 window.
The user must keep the mouse pointer inside that window during the
entire procedure.
Instructions for each key are printed to the terminal.
.PP
The resulting \f[B]keyto7\f[R] file is written in the current working
directory and must be present in that directory when
\f[B]funzyto770\f[R](1) is launched (unless a different file is
specified with the \f[B]-k\f[R] option).
.PP
This program only needs to be run once, or again whenever the keyboard
mapping needs to be redefined.
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
This program accepts no options.
.SH FILES
.TP
\f[I]keyto7\f[R]
Output keyboard layout file, written in the current directory.
Contains 68 X11 key codes, one per line.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Define the keyboard layout before running the emulator for the first
time:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
funzy_enterkey
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Follow the prompts in the terminal, pressing the corresponding key on
the physical keyboard for each TO7 key name displayed.
Once all 68 keys have been entered, the file \f[B]keyto7\f[R] is created
automatically.
.PP
Then launch the emulator:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
funzyto770
\f[R]
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
\f[B]funzyto770\f[R](1)
.SH BUGS
.PP
No known bugs.
